FOR MAC & WINDOWS:

* Download Arcadia Instant here:
    http://go.arcadiadata.com/Crush-the-Stack-Arcadia-Instant-Download-Campaign-Landing-Page.html

*** Import Dashboard:
1. Open Arcadia Instant Control Panel
2. Press 'Start', then 'Go'
3. Navigate to 'DATA' tab
4. Press '...' (next to 'NEW DATASET' and 'ADD DATA' tabs)
    * Choose 'Import Visual Artifacts'
5. Browse for current_visuals.json; Choose Private or Public.
6. Press 'IMPORT', then navigate to 'VISUALS' tab
    * Importing may require adding new datasets; steps can be found below.
7. Open HPotter dashboard; the dashboard should then display.


NOTE: Datasets can be used to create new visuals when the dashboard
      is open.

*** Add new datasets(DB tables):
1. Go to 'DATA' tab, then 'NEW CONNECTION'
2. Create a new data connection.
    * Connection type: SQLite
    * Connection name: HPotter
    * Basic
    * File name: path to main.db
    * Test connection, press 'CONNECT' when test passes
3. Press 'NEW DATASET', create data sets for each table.
    * Dataset title: table name
    * Select Database: main
    * Select Table: table name
    * 'CREATE'


*** To edit/add visuals to the dashboard:
1. Open HPotter dashboard under 'VISUALS' tab
2. Press 'EDIT'
3. Add/move/update/delete visuals.
    * Style of each visual & overall style of dashboard can be changed
4. Make sure to press 'SAVE'!


*** To create new current_visuals.json
1. Open Hpotter dashboard
2. Press '...' (next to 'SAVE')
3. Press 'EXPORT'
4. Create Filename, then EXPORT


* When finished: press 'Stop' then 'Quit' in AI Control Panel
